{
  "texts": [
    "Typically, color constancy processing can be accomplished in two separate steps.",
    "First, the estimation of the light source in RGB space is accomplished.",
    "The estimated light source is then used to transform the image to minimize the effect of the light source.",
    "The Shades of Gray method, which is the most commonly used method for dermatoscopic image processing, employs Minkowski's paradigm for light source estimation.",
    "It uses Minkowski's paradigm to estimate the light source."
  ]
}